2026-04-21 01:34:35 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 6 internal wiring between Control Input Cable (+) 6 and Control Switch 6'] hypothesis_explanation='The upstream diagnostics show that +12 V is present correctly through Control Module 5, but from Control Module 6 onward the +12 V line drops to nearly 0 V with no polarity inversion. Inspection of Control Module 6 reveals that the internal green power‑flow indicator LED and its series resistor are physically missing, and more critically, Control Input Cable (+) 6 is not connected to Control Switch 6. This open circuit on the positive line prevents +12 V from propagating to Control Module 6’s output and on to the load, explaining why all downstream indicators and the lamp remain off despite a good battery and all switches being ON. The root cause is therefore the open connection / mis‑wiring inside Control Module 6 between its positive input cable and the internal switch path.'
